      "patient_reported_reason": "Sudden onset shortness of breath and right-sided chest pain",
      "clinician_notes": "Subjective: 54-year-old female with 12-hour history of pleuritic right-sided chest pain and progressive dyspnoea. Long-haul flight 8 days ago. Right calf swelling and tenderness. No haemoptysis.\n\nObjective: HR 108 bpm, BP 128/82 mmHg, SpO2 89% on RA, RR 22/min, T 37.2 C. Reduced air entry right base. Right calf +3 cm vs left. D-dimer 4.2 ug/mL elevated. CTPA: bilateral pulmonary emboli, right lower lobe predominance, no haemodynamic compromise.\n\nAssessment: Pulmonary embolism (high probability, Wells 7.5). Concomitant right popliteal DVT confirmed on doppler.\n\nPlan: Rivaroxaban 15 mg BD for 21 days, then 20 mg OD with evening meal indefinitely. Admit for monitoring. Thrombophilia screen. Haematology and respiratory outpatient follow-up.",
